<p>London.</p>
<p>During his sermon on Ascension Day he made very definite statements regarding a Heaven which is not far away, but a spirit world all round us.  I felt it very keenly in the bright spring sunshine, despite the warlike appearance of two bulging observation balloons &amp; the shells bursting a few hundred yards away.</p>
<p>The fact we are simply material flesh &amp; blood actuated by personalities is very clear to me now.  When one does the personality survives &amp; becomes a member of the spirit world.</p>
